age from our test. For line 52, it seems we might not need to make any changes. However, it could be a good idea to document our process by adding a test for DatatypeConverter if it’s available. That way, even if we don't cover line 52, we still provide clarity and thoroughness! I want to ensure we're covering all bases.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Evaluating Java final answer**\\\\n\\\\nThe final answer should indicate that line 52 is unreachable because the static initializer checks `DatatypeConverter` only if the Java 8 `Base64` branch fails. Since `java.util.Base64` is part of `java.base` on all supported runtimes for version 2.17.1, missing it would require an unnatural environment or shadowing JDK classes. I should mention that existing tests in `Base64ConverterTest` cover 4 out of 5 cases, and that there is a previous uncommitted file to address.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"No additional test was added for the remaining call site.\\n\\nThe remaining uncovered site:\\n\\n- `Base64Converter.<clinit>(Base64Converter.java:52)`\\n\\nis the legacy fallback path:\\n\\n```java\\nLoaderUtil.loadClass(\\\"javax.xml.bind.DatatypeConverter\\\")\\n```\\n\\nThat branch only executes if the Java 8+ `java.util.Base64` path fails during static initialization. On the supported runtime for `log4j-core:2.17.1`, `java.util.Base64` is always available from `java.base`, so line 52 is not reachable through normal supported Log4j public API behavior.\\n\\nForcing that branch would require an unsupported runtime or artificial class-loading manipulation/shadowing of JDK classes, which would violate the task constraints. The existing added test remains the appropriate supported coverage path:\\n\\n- `tests/src/org.apache.logging.log4j/log4j-core/2.17.1/src/test/java/org_apache_logging_log4j/log4j_core/Base64ConverterTest.java`\\n\\nIt covers the supported `Base64:` byte-array conversion path and reached the Java `Base64` reflective initialization and decode call sites.\", \"textSignature\": \"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_0655aa627cbc877a016a26056c25a88195b97ed47319e27300\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 27560, \"output\": 1782, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 29342, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"stop\", \"timestamp\": 1780876612874, \"responseId\": \"resp_0655aa627cbc877a016a2605468a848195b436a291e1d1e097\"}, \"toolResults\": []}\n[recv] agent_end\n[send] get_state\n[recv] get_state success\n  sessionFile: ../../../../../../.pi/agent/sessions/--home-jovan-Work-graalvm-reachability-metadata-forge-local_repositories-forge_worktrees-2160-8295e0c9--/2026-06-07T23-44-07-627Z_017c93e9-36da-4190-9d26-0c8e968855c8.jsonl\n  sessionId: 017c93e9-36da-4190-9d26-0c8e968855c8\n[send] get_session_stats\n[recv] get_session_stats success\n  tokens: input=96303 output=6357 cacheRead=428032 cacheWrite=0 total=530692\n\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
