ing manipulation/shadowing of JDK classes, which would violate the task constraints. The existing added test remains the appropriate supported coverage path:\\n\\n- `tests/src/org.apache.logging.log4j/log4j-core/2.17.1/src/test/java/org_apache_logging_log4j/log4j_core/Base64ConverterTest.java`\\n\\nIt covers the supported `Base64:` byte-array conversion path and reached the Java `Base64` reflective initialization and decode call sites.\", \"textSignature\": \"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_0655aa627cbc877a016a26056c25a88195b97ed47319e27300\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 27560, \"output\": 1782, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 29342, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"stop\", \"timestamp\": 1780876612874, \"responseId\": \"resp_0655aa627cbc877a016a2605468a848195b436a291e1d1e097\"}, \"toolResults\": []}\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
